title: Breaking Down Southeast Asia’s M&A and IPO Market in 2020
text: Dec.08 -- Jake Robson, partner at Morrison & Foerster, discusses his IPO outlook for 2020 in Southeast Asia and what he’s seeing in M&A.

title: Asia markets seesaw on caution as traders look for potential trade deal
text: Asian markets seesawed on Monday as traders cautiously await the progress on a trade deal before the December 15 deadline for a new round of US tariffs on Chinese goods.

title: Oil prices stumble on weak China exports hangover
text: Oil prices fell on Monday after data showing China's overall exports of goods and services shrank for a fourth straight month, sending shivers through a market already concerned about damage being down to global demand by the Sino-U.S. trade war.

title: The U.S. Dominates New Oil And Gas Production
text: Already the largest oil and gas producer, the U.S. is set to increase its share of ~17% of global oil production and ~23% of gas.

title: OPEC Left With Limited Options
text: OPEC surprised some by announcing additional production cuts at its most recent meeting. But the cartel likely felt it had limited options.

title: Why a rate hike could surprise the market in 2020
text: Wells Fargo Securities' Michael Schumacher speculates November's blowout jobs report may signal the economy is stronger than the consensus thinks.

title: Sharp Market Decline Holds Key Levels
text: New tariffs on Brazil and Argentina pushed stocks sharply lower at the start of the week but market technician Tom Aspray discusses how some of the key methods he uses indicated that the market had reached important support. This set the stage for the rally into the end of the week.

title: As Fed reiterates rate pause, forecasts likely to be blown off course
text: Friday’s booming U.S. jobs report should give the Federal Reserve all it needs to stick to its plan not to cut interest rates further in the near future, so when U.S. central bankers meet this week, most of the focus will be on their outlook for next year and beyond.

title: Oil Is Moving Higher
text: Oil has rallied and will likely move to the $64-$65 level by the end of January.

title: U.S. banks' reluctance to lend cash may have caused repo shock: BIS
text: The unwillingness of the top four U.S. banks to lend cash combined with a burst of demand from hedge funds for secured funding could explain a recent spike in U.S. money market rates, the Bank for International Settlements said.

title: 'We are ready' to take Trump tariff threats to WTO: French finance minister
text: Washington is threatening to retaliate against France's digital tax on U.S. companies with heavy duties on imports of French champagne, cheeses and luxury handbags.

title: This is a crucial week for global trade
text: There's just one week to go before the United States is scheduled to impose a new round of tariffs on $156 billion of Chinese imports. Meanwhile, both sides are still working toward an elusive "phase one" trade deal that could bring some relief to battered global economies.

title: China November exports fall, but import growth hints of recovering demand
text: China's exports in November shrank for the fourth consecutive month, underscoring persistent pressures on manufacturers from the Sino-U.S. war but growth in imports may be a sign that Beijing's stimulus steps are helping to stoke demand.

title: The Next Recession May Come By Stealth
text: Since the financial crisis, the global economy has been reshaped by different forces, and the coming recession will be caused by factors totally different from those of the last one.

title: Aramco IPO Has Diverse Portfolio of Subscribers, Saudi Energy Minister Says
